<br>
After reformatting my computer, I updated all my drivers to the newest version and proceeded to load EQ. Now, however, EQ is insanely laggy. I play on a DSL connection, and fixed my datarate file, but am wondering if there's anything else I can do in the .ini file, or elsewhere? (The internet and all other internet programs work fine, run smoothly... I am fairly certain the problem lies within EQ's settings.)<br>
<br>
Examples of the type of lag I experience: Zoning takes upwards of three minutes, whereas before it only half a minute. Yes, I have caching on, but this three minute zoning takes place in zones I've already been to; I don't think its the caching. Also, when I open a window (i.e. the map, or the inventory screen) or a container (which I suppose would be similar to opening a window), EQ freezes for a second. And lastly, any interaction with NPC merchants is ridiculous in the response time, clicking/lag is unplayable.<br>
<br>
Anyone know what I can do? Please help, it is driving me Crazy!!!! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=derganpuppyeater>Dergan Puppyeater</A> at: 6/16/03 1:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=antoinnolouj>AntoinNolouj</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.personal.psu.edu/btk120/antoin.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>EQ doesn't drain your brain, honest.</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/17/03 6:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1669.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Reformatted, and now EQ lags like nothing else! Any idea</span><hr size=1> Also, when I open a window (i.e. the map, or the inventory screen) or a container (which I suppose would be similar to opening a window), EQ freezes for a second.<br>
<br>
I have this same problem, but it's a half-second for us.<br>
<br>
I would look for performance issues...do other games lag? (That might clue us in.)<br>
Do you have your swap file on its own partition/own drive? (Performance reasons.)<br>
Did you try other drivers? (latest drivers can have bugs.)<br>
Did you defragment the disk after patching? (try it.)<br>
Are you running drive compression?  (Turn it OFF, it's slow!)<br>
Are you using FAT16, FAT32, or NTFS for a file system? (they all aren't great, but at least NTFS is halfway decent)<br>
<br>
Is your hard disk on its own IDE/SCSI channel?  (Shared with a CD-ROM is bad news)<br>
Is your hard disk old? (like, using PIO old.  You want UDMA-capable disks)<br>
Does using the hard disk cause your CPU usage to spike? (This is a sign you're using PIO.  PIO is bad.)<br>
Is your hard disk controller too slow for the drive? (this is a hard question to answer)<br>
Is your system running hot?  (Check.)<br>
<br>
Is your network transfer fast from most other sites? (I hope so)<br>
Do other people access your computer remotely? (If not sure, find out)<br>
Are you sharing a connection? (That might do it.)<br>
Is your cablemodem/dsl model USB? (oddball question I know)<br>
<br>
All I can think of right now. <p>--Captain Antoin Nolouj<br>
